<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,151,609]" box="[199,401,259,285]" pageId="10" pageNumber="532">Female unknown.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,151,609]" box="[199,1376,295,321]" pageId="10" pageNumber="532">
Etymology. The specific epithet is derived from the Latin expression for the sky blue colour “ 
<emphasis box="[1248,1357,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="532">caeruleus</emphasis>
”.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,151,609]" box="[199,748,331,357]" pageId="10" pageNumber="532">
Distribution. 
<collectingCountry box="[349,744,331,357]" name="Democratic Republic of the Congo" pageId="10" pageNumber="532">Democratic Republic of the Congo</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,151,609]" pageId="10" pageNumber="532">
Differential diagnosis. Besides the blue colouration 
<taxonomicName authority="Bílý, 2020" authorityName="Bílý" authorityYear="2020" box="[784,1044,367,393]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Anthaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="532" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caerulea" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Haplanthaxia">
<emphasis box="[784,885,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="532">Anthaxia</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[902,929,367,392]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="532">H.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[946,1044,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="532">caerulea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1051,1141,367,393]" pageId="10" pageNumber="532">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1051,1141,367,393]" pageId="10" pageNumber="532" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
differs from other species of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kerremans" authorityYear="1898" box="[223,380,403,429]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Anthaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="532" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dispar" subGenus="Haplanthaxia">
<emphasis box="[223,248,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="532">A.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[264,292,403,428]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="532">H.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[308,380,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="532">dispar</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group by the sculpture of the pronotal disc which consists of the fine, transverse cells without central grains, truncate to weakly emarginate anal ventrite, relatively long elytra (twice as long as wide) and also by the different shape of aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[601,683,475,501]" captionStart="FIGS" captionStartId="8.[151,212,1796,1820]" captionTargetBox="[152,1436,1174,1771]" captionTargetId="figure-414@8.[151,1436,1173,1773]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGS. 16–22. Aedeagi (not in scale). 16—Anthaxia (Haplathaxia) aethiopica sp. nov., holotype; 17—A. (H.) caerulea sp. nov., holotype; 18—A. (H.) dispar Kerremans, 1898 (RSA, Limpopo); 19—A. (H.) keniae Théry, 1941 (Kenya, Kiserian); 20—A. (H.) komareki Obenberger, 1931, holotype; 21—A. (H.) occidentalis sp. nov., holotype; 22—A. (H.) pilifrons Kerremans, 1898, holotype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4408013" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4408013/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="532">Fig. 17</figureCitation>
) and male metatibiae (
<figureCitation box="[939,1023,475,501]" captionStart="FIGS" captionStartId="9.[151,212,1917,1941]" captionTargetBox="[155,1432,1318,1893]" captionTargetId="figure-459@9.[151,1435,1317,1894]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGS. 23–28. Male metatibiae (not in scale). 23—Anthaxia (Haplathaxia) aethiopica sp. nov., holotype; 24—A. (H.) caerulea sp. nov., holotype; 25—A. (H.) dispar Kerremans, 1898 (RSA, Limpopo); 26—A. (H.) keniae Théry, 1941 (Kenya, Kiserian); 27—A. (H.) occidentalis sp. nov., holotype; 28—A. (H.) pilifrons Kerremans, 1898, holotype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4408017" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4408017/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="532">Fig. 24</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,151,609]" pageId="10" pageNumber="532">
<taxonomicName authority="Bílý, 2020" authorityName="Bílý" authorityYear="2020" box="[199,459,511,537]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Anthaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="532" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caerulea" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Haplanthaxia">
<emphasis box="[199,300,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="532">Anthaxia</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[317,345,511,536]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="532">H.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[361,459,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="532">caerulea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[466,557,511,537]" pageId="10" pageNumber="532">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[466,557,511,537]" pageId="10" pageNumber="532" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
seems to be distributed in the humid, tropical part of 
<collectingCountry box="[1162,1220,511,537]" name="Democratic Republic of the Congo" pageId="10" pageNumber="532">DRC</collectingCountry>
unlike the sympatric 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kerremans" authorityYear="1898" box="[188,346,547,573]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Anthaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="532" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dispar" subGenus="Haplanthaxia">
<emphasis box="[188,213,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="532">A.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[229,257,547,572]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="532">H.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[274,346,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="532">dispar</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
which follows the less humid, savanna biotopes of the eastern and southern parts of 
<collectingCountry box="[1303,1364,547,573]" name="Democratic Republic of the Congo" pageId="10" pageNumber="532">DRC</collectingCountry>
. More specimens of 
<taxonomicName authority="Bílý, 2020" authorityName="Bílý" authorityYear="2020" box="[305,487,583,609]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Anthaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="532" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caerulea" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Haplanthaxia">
<emphasis box="[305,330,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="532">A.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[346,373,583,608]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="532">H.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[389,487,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="532">caerulea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[494,584,583,609]" pageId="10" pageNumber="532">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[494,584,583,609]" pageId="10" pageNumber="532" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
are needed, of course, for any further speculations.
</paragraph>
